    <span>5 min read</span>
  </div>
    <h1>Best Robo-Advisors in Canada (2026)</h1>
    <h2>The Canadian Robo-Advisor Landscape</h2>
    <p>Robo-advisors have fundamentally changed retail investing in Canada. By using algorithms to build and rebalance ETF portfolios, they offer a hands-off investment experience at a fraction of the cost of traditional mutual funds. For investors who want market returns without the hassle of manual rebalancing or individual stock picking, robo-advisors represent the optimal blend of cost-efficiency and convenience.</p>
    <p>Below is our compiled list of the top robo-advisors available to Canadian investors in 2026, ranked by a combination of fee structure, platform usability, portfolio options, and account support.</p>

    <h2>Top Platforms Ranked</h2>

    <div class="advisor-card">
      <div class="advisor-header">
        <div class="advisor-title">1. Wealthsimple Invest</div>
        <div class="advisor-badge">Best Overall</div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-stats">
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Management Fee</div>
          <div class="stat-value">0.40% - 0.50%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Min. Investment</div>
          <div class="stat-value">$0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Avg. ETF MER</div>
          <div class="stat-value">~0.15%</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-desc">
        <p>Wealthsimple remains the dominant player in the Canadian robo-advisor space. It offers a beautifully designed, intuitive app and absolutely zero minimum investment, making it highly accessible. Their portfolios are globally diversified across thousands of companies using low-cost index ETFs. They offer standard, Socially Responsible Investing (SRI), and Halal portfolios.</p>
        <p>While their base fee of 0.50% drops to 0.40% for accounts over $100,000 (Wealthsimple Premium), it is not the absolute cheapest on the market. However, their seamless integration with Wealthsimple Cash, Crypto, and Tax makes it the ultimate all-in-one financial hub for Canadians.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="advisor-card">
      <div class="advisor-header">
        <div class="advisor-title">2. Questwealth Portfolios</div>
        <div class="advisor-badge">Lowest Fees</div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-stats">
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Management Fee</div>
          <div class="stat-value">0.20% - 0.25%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Min. Investment</div>
          <div class="stat-value">$1,000</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Avg. ETF MER</div>
          <div class="stat-value">~0.11% - 0.23%</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-desc">
        <p>Offered by Questrade, Questwealth Portfolios boasts the lowest management fees of any major Canadian robo-advisor. They charge just 0.25% for balances under $100,000, and an incredibly low 0.20% for balances above that threshold. Over decades of compounding, these fee savings can add up to thousands of dollars.</p>
        <p>Unlike purely passive competitors, Questwealth uses <em>active management</em>. Their portfolio managers adjust the ETF allocations based on market research and economic trends. While active management doesn't guarantee outperformance, the structural cost advantage makes Questwealth highly compelling for fee-conscious investors.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="advisor-card">
      <div class="advisor-header">
        <div class="advisor-title">3. Justwealth</div>
        <div class="advisor-badge">Best for Customization & RESPs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-stats">
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Management Fee</div>
          <div class="stat-value">0.40% - 0.50%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Min. Investment</div>
          <div class="stat-value">$5,000</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Avg. ETF MER</div>
          <div class="stat-value">~0.20%</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-desc">
        <p>Justwealth stands out by offering over 80 different portfolio configurations, significantly more than its competitors. They provide highly tailored portfolios for specific goals, including US-dollar portfolios, income-generating portfolios, and tax-efficient non-registered accounts.</p>
        <p>They are particularly renowned for their Target Date RESP portfolios. Instead of maintaining a static risk profile, the RESP portfolio automatically shifts to more conservative fixed-income investments as the child approaches university age, perfectly aligning with the drawdown schedule of education savings.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="advisor-card">
      <div class="advisor-header">
        <div class="advisor-title">4. RBC InvestEase</div>
        <div class="advisor-badge">Best Bank-Owned</div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-stats">
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Management Fee</div>
          <div class="stat-value">0.50%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Min. Investment</div>
          <div class="stat-value">$100</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Avg. ETF MER</div>
          <div class="stat-value">~0.11% - 0.16%</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-desc">
        <p>For investors who prefer the security and integration of a Big Five bank, RBC InvestEase is the clear winner. Unlike many bank mutual funds that charge 2.00%+ MERs, InvestEase charges a competitive 0.50% management fee. The portfolios are built exclusively using low-cost iShares ETFs by BlackRock.</p>
        <p>It integrates seamlessly into the existing RBC online banking dashboard, allowing current RBC clients to view their investments alongside their checking accounts and mortgages. They also offer Standard and Responsible Investing (ESG) portfolio options.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="advisor-card">
      <div class="advisor-header">
        <div class="advisor-title">5. CI Direct Investing</div>
        <div class="advisor-badge">Best for High Net Worth</div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-stats">
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Management Fee</div>
          <div class="stat-value">0.35% - 0.60%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Min. Investment</div>
          <div class="stat-value">$1,000</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-box">
          <div class="stat-label">Avg. ETF MER</div>
          <div class="stat-value">~0.18% - 0.28%</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advisor-desc">
        <p>Formerly known as WealthBar, CI Direct Investing offers a hybrid model that blends robo-advisor automation with access to dedicated financial advisors. Their fee structure is tiered: 0.60% on the first $150k, dropping to 0.40% on the next $350k, and 0.35% above $500k.</p>
        <p>While their base fee is higher, they offer premium financial planning services and access to private investment portfolios (like real estate and private equity funds) that are typically reserved for institutional or ultra-high-net-worth investors, making them an excellent choice for larger, more complex estates.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is a robo-advisor?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">A robo-advisor is an automated investment platform that builds and manages a diversified portfolio of exchange-traded funds (ETFs) for you based on your risk tolerance and financial goals, typically charging lower fees than traditional mutual funds or financial advisors.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What are the typical fees for a Canadian robo-advisor?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">In Canada, robo-advisor management fees usually range from 0.20% to 0.50% of your total assets under management (AUM) per year. In addition to this management fee, you will also pay the Management Expense Ratios (MERs) of the underlying ETFs, which average around 0.10% to 0.20%.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is my money safe with a Canadian robo-advisor?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, funds held with major Canadian robo-advisors are safe. The cash and securities in your accounts are held by custodian brokerages that are members of the Canadian Investor Protection Fund (CIPF), which protects your assets up to $1 million per account type in the unlikely event the firm goes insolvent.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can I hold RRSPs and TFSAs in a robo-advisor account?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Absolutely. Almost all Canadian robo-advisors support registered accounts, including Registered Retirement Savings Plans (RRSPs), Tax-Free Savings Accounts (TFSAs), First Home Savings Accounts (FHSAs), and Registered Education Savings Plans (RESPs).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How does Questwealth Portfolios differ from Wealthsimple?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Questwealth Portfolios uses an active management approach, where their portfolio managers adjust the ETF weightings based on market conditions, and charges a lower management fee (0.25% or 0.20% for larger balances). Wealthsimple uses a strictly passive, rules-based indexing approach and charges slightly higher fees (0.50% or 0.40% for larger balances) but offers a more integrated financial ecosystem with no minimum investment.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

